==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|kwĭt}}, {{IPA|/kwɪt/}}, {{SAMPA|/kwIt/}}
* {{audio|en-us-quit.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|quits|quitting|'''quit''' ''or'' '''[[quitted]]'''}}

# To [[stop]] doing something.
# To [[give up]] a [[habit]].
# To [[leave]] a [[locality]].
# ([[w:Reflexive verb|reflexive]]) - to conduct oneself, to behave.
# {{past of|[[quit]]}}

====Quotations====
* {{seeCites}}

====Usage notes====
* The past tense of ''quit'' is now ''quit'' for most speakers and writers; dictionaries usually allow ''quitted'' as an alternative, but it is rare or nonexistent in North America and Australia, and outnumbered by ''quit'' by about 16 to 1 in the [http://www.natcorp.ox.ac.uk/ British National Corpus].  Quitted is more commonly used to mean "left". ''ie. She quitted her job.''
* In sense 1. this is a [[catenative]] verb that takes the ''gerund (-ing)''. See [[Appendix:English catenative verbs]]

